          <msContents>
            <summary>Collection of hymns, mantras, and praises to the Sun god (Āditya also called Sūrya) used for private or public recitation, meditation, and prayer. presented as a conversation between the legendary prince Arjuna and the Hindu deity Kṛṣṇa.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Ādityahṛdayastotra</title>
              <title type="vernacular">आदित्यहृदयस्तोत्र</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>scribe</resp>
                <persName type="authority">Paraśurāma (son of Mahādeva Dāḍekara)</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrībhaviṣyottarapurāṇe śrīkṛṣṇārjunasaṃvāde ādityahṛdayastotraṃ saṃpūrṇaṃ // śrīkṛṣṇārpaṇam astu // cha // śake 1656 ānaṃdanāmasaṃvatsare mārgaśīrṣaṣuklapaṃcamyām idam pustakaṃ dāḍekaropanāmmāmahādevātmajaparaśurāmeṇa likhitaṃ // svārthaṃ paropakārārthaṃ ca // cha // śrīsavitāsūryanārāyaṇārpaṇam astu // (f. 21r-22v).</colophon>
